{
  "texts": [
    "Any tool developed will show errors while in use, but the consequences of such errors might have several implications that are not currently foreseen.",
    "To account for true positives, our approach was to compute the recall value which for BERT showed an average value of 97.30% with a minimum value of 74% in the fine-tuning process.",
    "While the percentage of true positives is promising, it will certainly vary according to the task and in non-controlled environments.",
    "Furthermore, if the average value is considered, there are still 2.7% of wrongly classified observations.",
    "As Lund & Wang, (2023) have identified, AI tools have tremendous impacts in society particularly in academia and education."
  ]
}